This program provides hardware control for the SDR-1000 for Windows (VS2005, Cygwin)
and Linux environments including USB Adapter support.

To build this project, browse to the \build folder and choose the appropriate
subfolder based on your OS/compiler.  Under linux and cygwin, simply run 'make'.
For Visual Studio 2005, there is a complete project file.

The outputs will be put in the \bin folder.


Requirements:

Linux:
libusb
build-essentials

Cygwin:
libusb-win32
porttalk.sys in \system32\drivers
gcc
g++

VS2005:
Visual Studio 2005 (any version including the free Express edition)